IMX I2C manager

%C [options]

Options:
-a addr     Own address (default: 0)
-c clock    Input clock (default: 66500000)
-h prio     Priority of event associated to I2C interrupt handler (default: 21)
-i intr     I2C port interrupt number
-I if       I2C number, specifies default reg. addr. and intr. (1|2|3, def: 1)
-p addr     I2C port register physical address
-s slave    Slave address (default: 0x38)
-t factor   Slave response timeout factor when waiting for a slave device to respond.
            Represents what factor to multiply the minimum theoretical transaction
            time by before timing out (default: 20 times)
-v          Verbose
-y ns       Bus busy timeout when initiating a transaction (default: 500000 ns)

Generic options:
--b bus_speed    Bus speed
--m max_msg_len  Length to set resmgr receive buffer (default: 128 bytes)
--n nparts       Minimum number of iov_t's in resmgr context (default: 2)
--u unit         Unit number. Number to append to device name prefix /dev/i2c
                 (default: 0)
